      "comment": "PHOENIX TAN (1) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing fifth over 450m Shepparton in 25.59. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Has winning claims on her best figures. ALFREDO (2) settled midfield in the run and boxed on to finish there when 4th (25.59) at Ballarat. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from three starts. Likely to play a prominent role. OFF THE BEER (4) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (30.79) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. In the mix. MISTER MANFREDI (8) cannot be underestimated.",
